Anyway, who's that coming?
Almost no one understands what's going on and why you have to fight in this war.
"The lack of facts," Mr. Englund notes, "is filled with conjectures, assumptions, hopes, fears, obsessions, conspiracy theories, dreams, nightmares and rumours".
"Beauty and sorrow" tracks the fate of people like Florence Farmborough, an English nurse in the Russian army, and Richard Stumpf, a young sailor of the German high seas.
Their stories are mainly drawn from memoirs, letters, and other material already published.
Their lives may be scary or exciting, but they are extremely alive thanks to Mr. Englund ' s small moments and partial details.
