He reported that, on average, Mexicans were 65 per cent descendants of American Indians, 30 per cent descendants of Europeans and five per cent descendants of Africans, a condition that affected genes associated with diabetes and excess weight.
He explained that the main effect of obesity genetics is the inability of the body to burn the excess energy that we consume (calories) and it is delayed in the form of fat.
The researcher explained that the immediate benefit to participants was a comprehensive assessment of children, which could determine whether they had any excess weight or obesity.
