During the same period, it will be necessary to fill the increasing scarcity of fossil resources in order to continue to generate electricity at all times, bearing in mind the crucial need to reduce greenhouse gas emissions in order to address the climate imbalance, a theme that has disappeared from the environmental debate.
The Fukushima accident doesn't change any of these factors.
That is why Germany remains alone in its decision to renounce nuclear energy.
This is not the case of Belgium, which makes its decision conditional on the need to find a source capable of replacing nuclear power, or of Switzerland, which intends to build only the most modern reactors.
On the other hand, the United Kingdom, the Czech Republic, Finland, Poland, the Netherlands, Sweden, South Africa, China, India, Brazil are only a few of those who are resolutely pursuing their projects.
